WEBVTT

01:38.160 --> 01:40.480
EPISODE 30

01:40.960 --> 01:46.040
He's incredible for holding
Erxi like that. It's so sensational!

01:46.840 --> 01:48.400
Come here, Weiwei...

01:52.800 --> 01:54.520
Should we go get Erxi back?

01:54.600 --> 01:56.280
Are you silly or what?

01:56.360 --> 01:58.160
Can't you feel

01:58.240 --> 02:01.240
the love hearts floating
around Erxi and Cao Guang?

02:01.680 --> 02:04.200
It's a classic prelude
to a budding romance.

02:15.240 --> 02:16.760
Haven't you ever been in love?

02:19.480 --> 02:20.640
Have I?

02:22.480 --> 02:24.840
Sorry, I'll take her
for further education.

02:35.080 --> 02:36.520
Will they really be okay?

02:36.600 --> 02:39.600
Don't worry.
They didn't damage school property.

02:41.080 --> 02:43.200
I'm not worried about school property.

02:48.280 --> 02:52.840
Mr. Xiao Nai, why do you have time
to come see us take graduation photos?

02:52.960 --> 02:54.600
Weren't you being interviewed?

02:54.720 --> 02:57.600
You know so much about me.

02:57.920 --> 02:59.480
You even saw my interview.

03:00.800 --> 03:02.960
I only watched five, six,
seven or eight minutes.

03:03.040 --> 03:06.560
That's 26 minutes total.
So you saw the main point?

03:11.200 --> 03:13.640
When did I agree to be your fiancée?

03:16.520 --> 03:17.440
You tell me.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.880
Hi, are you Mr. Xiao Nai?

03:21.120 --> 03:24.280
I'm a fan and a dedicated player of
"A New Chinese Ghost Story."

03:24.360 --> 03:26.640
Can I have your autograph?

03:27.040 --> 03:28.800
My autograph won't mean much,

03:28.880 --> 03:30.440
but thanks for supporting our game.

03:30.520 --> 03:32.880
Yes, I'll keep supporting it.

03:32.960 --> 03:37.720
We'll get out of your hair now.
Bye, Mr. Xiao.

03:44.280 --> 03:47.000
Let's go, fiancé.
Take my luggage to Xiaoling's place.

03:49.600 --> 03:53.080
Weiwei, when did I agree
to be your fiancé?

03:56.480 --> 03:57.920
I know you well.

03:58.480 --> 04:02.400
I think I can transport
your luggage for you. Let's go.

04:16.959 --> 04:19.240
The four of us
will still be living together.

04:19.440 --> 04:21.800
We just move from the dorm
to Xiaoling's place.

04:22.160 --> 04:24.160
It doesn't feel like we've graduated.

04:24.440 --> 04:26.680
Plus, the office is so close.

04:29.680 --> 04:32.240
Dazhong doesn't mind
you girls living with Xiaoling?

04:33.480 --> 04:34.320
Why would he mind?

04:36.160 --> 04:37.360
Get in.

04:47.120 --> 04:50.040
Dazhong doesn't mind it, but I do.

05:00.880 --> 05:02.680
My bedding and pillow

05:02.760 --> 05:04.400
are at Xiaoling's place.

05:05.640 --> 05:06.480
Use mine.

05:08.960 --> 05:10.360
You only have one pillow.

05:10.680 --> 05:11.520
It'll do.

05:14.360 --> 05:17.160
Sleeping on the couch too often
can ruin your spine.

05:24.440 --> 05:26.120
Who says I'm sleeping on the couch?

05:53.240 --> 05:54.480
You promised.

05:55.640 --> 05:58.840
I know. I won't.

06:15.440 --> 06:16.840
When will you let me graduate?

06:18.240 --> 06:19.400
Graduate from what?

06:20.320 --> 06:24.040
Haven't you made me study
voluntary control for two years?

06:24.760 --> 06:25.720
Voluntary control?

06:29.840 --> 06:31.080
Self-control.

06:55.120 --> 06:58.560
Be quiet. Don't move.

07:10.480 --> 07:14.040
After the graduation ceremony in two days,
let's go to Wuhan.

07:17.560 --> 07:18.400
Okay.

07:19.480 --> 07:20.960
We'll drive.

07:23.240 --> 07:28.120
Drive? Why? Wuhan is so far.

07:30.280 --> 07:34.760
Anyway, I'm not moving back
to work in Wuhan,

07:36.840 --> 07:40.520
and I don't have much luggage.

07:43.640 --> 07:45.120
You grew up there.

07:45.920 --> 07:49.560
You'll have stuff to bring back.
It's more convenient to drive.

07:53.320 --> 07:57.160
So, you're driving,

07:57.840 --> 08:00.760
not because we're moving stuff home,

08:01.600 --> 08:03.080
but to move stuff here?

08:08.800 --> 08:09.640
That's right.

08:11.800 --> 08:17.160
Weiwei, I have decided
never to return you to your parents.

08:36.840 --> 08:39.400
Old Bei, they'll be here soon.

08:39.480 --> 08:41.559
Go greet them at the entrance.

08:42.880 --> 08:44.440
Why bother?

08:44.520 --> 08:46.920
Isn't Weiwei with him?
They won't be lost.

08:50.120 --> 08:52.080
It's our son-in-law's first visit.

08:52.320 --> 08:54.480
Why are you looking like that?

08:55.480 --> 08:58.920
Son-in-law? Did I give my consent?

08:59.160 --> 09:01.800
He's not our son-in-law, until I say so.

09:05.800 --> 09:07.640
What's with Weiwei anyway?

09:08.240 --> 09:10.960
She's just graduated
and she wants to get married.

09:11.040 --> 09:13.080
With her looks and her background,

09:13.160 --> 09:14.680
she can have any man!

09:14.760 --> 09:16.880
Why is she in a hurry to get married?

09:18.880 --> 09:20.240
It's infuriating.

09:25.320 --> 09:28.400
I'm telling you,
in terms of our future son-in-law,

09:28.480 --> 09:30.880
I already have a comprehensive
assessment plan.

09:32.640 --> 09:35.760
If he fails in one category,
there's no marriage.

09:39.760 --> 09:42.160
Don't you jump on the bandwagon
and ruin my plan!

09:45.960 --> 09:48.120
Just watch your ball game.

09:48.840 --> 09:51.280
I want no part in your stupid plan.

09:51.920 --> 09:55.560
I've seen our son-in-law's photo.
I'm very pleased.

09:55.640 --> 09:56.880
Photo?

09:57.280 --> 10:00.280
Don't you scare him off, I'm telling you.

10:00.360 --> 10:03.040
Or you can spend
the rest of your life alone.

10:03.520 --> 10:06.440
If you won't go greet them, I will.

10:06.600 --> 10:08.400
Hey...

10:09.120 --> 10:11.640
Why would you pick a son-in-law
from a photo?

10:13.760 --> 10:16.120
Can a pretty face alone support a family?

10:17.840 --> 10:21.840
Long hair and short-sighted, indeed.
You've always been like that.

10:26.120 --> 10:30.320
Can he be more handsome than me?
I don't think so!

10:33.360 --> 10:36.200
Make a left, okay. It's straight up ahead.

10:39.920 --> 10:41.000
My mom's here.

10:58.400 --> 10:59.720
Auntie.

11:02.120 --> 11:05.040
- Mom!
- My baby girl!

11:05.720 --> 11:06.920
- Have you missed me?
- Yes.

11:07.160 --> 11:09.320
How was the drive? Are you tired?

11:09.960 --> 11:11.440
I wasn't the one driving.

11:11.520 --> 11:13.920
You're so silly. Introduce us.

11:16.640 --> 11:19.040
Mom, let me introduce you.
This is Xiao Nai.

11:19.760 --> 11:22.200
Xiao Nai, this is my mom, Chen Fang.

11:22.280 --> 11:25.640
- How are you, Auntie?
- Good, very good.

11:26.320 --> 11:27.400
Where's Dad?

11:27.880 --> 11:28.720
Your Dad's at home.

11:29.160 --> 11:30.720
You must be tired from the drive.

11:30.800 --> 11:32.200
Come on, let's go eat.

11:32.480 --> 11:34.360
Sure. Let me park the car.

11:51.640 --> 11:54.600
- You didn't have to bring anything.
- It's a must.

11:55.040 --> 11:56.320
Come, let's go home.

11:56.840 --> 11:57.800
Let's go.

11:59.120 --> 12:00.920
- Is it heavy? I'll help you.
- It's fine.

12:11.880 --> 12:15.760
Stamina, endurance, IQ, EQ...

12:27.640 --> 12:29.640
Here... Come on...

12:29.720 --> 12:32.200
- Make yourself at home.
- Wear your shoes inside.

12:32.280 --> 12:34.440
Old Bei, they're here.

12:35.920 --> 12:36.800
Dad!

12:37.360 --> 12:41.760
Dad, let me introduce you.
This is Xiao Nai.

12:41.840 --> 12:43.600
Xiao Nai, this is my Dad.

12:44.000 --> 12:46.640
- Hello, Uncle.
- Hi.

12:48.080 --> 12:50.600
Dad, Xiao Nai brought you nice tea.

12:52.640 --> 12:55.560
Their tea has nothing on the tea here.

12:59.480 --> 13:02.360
Fine... Since you already brought it,
just put it there.

13:03.480 --> 13:04.960
He bought a lot of stuff,

13:05.040 --> 13:07.880
including caterpillar fungus
and bird's nest for Mom.

13:08.240 --> 13:09.520
Thank you.

13:09.600 --> 13:11.480
You bought such expensive ingredients,

13:11.560 --> 13:13.040
but I don't know how to use them.

13:13.440 --> 13:15.280
I'll write down the recipes.

13:15.840 --> 13:19.000
Sure... There's no hurry. Let's eat.

13:19.320 --> 13:21.600
Go wash your hands. Let's eat.

13:21.920 --> 13:23.560
The restroom is this way. Come on.

13:25.320 --> 13:27.200
Old Bei, why are you acting like this?

13:28.920 --> 13:30.840
Can't you show some dignity?

13:30.920 --> 13:32.920
You act like you've never seen
caterpillar fungus!

13:33.000 --> 13:35.840
- I'll go serve the dishes.
- Hurry!

13:46.880 --> 13:49.280
Here. It's clean.

13:57.240 --> 13:58.480
His height is okay.

14:02.080 --> 14:03.520
Here are the crawfish.

14:04.320 --> 14:05.160
Here.

14:06.360 --> 14:09.040
Crawfish are in season now.

14:09.120 --> 14:10.960
Xiao Nai, Wuhan-style crawfish

14:11.040 --> 14:12.640
is different from other places.

14:12.720 --> 14:15.680
Steaming is the best way
to keep the sweetness of crawfish.

14:15.760 --> 14:16.720
Try it.

14:19.000 --> 14:19.840
Here.

14:23.200 --> 14:26.320
Dad, have some, too.

14:27.480 --> 14:29.640
Here's a big one for you. Eat up...

14:32.000 --> 14:35.560
I'm telling you,
my dad's dipping sauce is the best.

14:36.920 --> 14:38.080
It's okay.

14:39.800 --> 14:42.480
Eat up, Xiao Nai.

14:43.120 --> 14:45.120
I don't cook as well as Weiwei's Dad,

14:45.200 --> 14:48.360
but I also make authentic
Wuhan-style dishes.

14:49.760 --> 14:51.160
Thanks, Auntie. It's good.

14:53.280 --> 14:57.480
Xiao, Weiwei tells me,
you're in the business of making games?

14:58.360 --> 14:59.520
That's right.

15:00.160 --> 15:03.120
The job doesn't sound very reliable.

15:04.720 --> 15:06.440
Why isn't it reliable?

15:06.520 --> 15:07.720
Aren't I in the same business?

15:08.160 --> 15:10.880
You're not the same.
Eat your food. I'm asking him.

15:12.720 --> 15:15.360
Anyway, since you're in that business,

15:15.520 --> 15:17.480
your future husband

15:17.560 --> 15:19.480
should have
a comparatively stable job, no?

15:20.000 --> 15:22.280
Games are the earliest products we made.

15:22.360 --> 15:25.400
In the past two years,
we have expanded into other software.

15:28.080 --> 15:29.960
That's even worse.

15:31.280 --> 15:34.720
You should stay focused in a job, no?

15:35.080 --> 15:38.160
If you're doing one thing here,
one thing there,

15:38.480 --> 15:40.480
that's not being focused.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.480
Old Bei, you just got a new job.

15:44.560 --> 15:46.720
Why don't you say you're not focused?

15:46.800 --> 15:49.520
No, I... How am I not focused?

15:49.640 --> 15:51.320
How is this the same as getting a new job?

15:51.840 --> 15:52.920
How is not the same?

15:53.120 --> 15:55.320
You always use double standards.

15:55.400 --> 15:56.760
You're nitpicking.

15:57.000 --> 16:00.080
- Why can't you talk nicely?
- How am I not talking nicely?

16:00.160 --> 16:01.240
In front of...

16:01.840 --> 16:03.880
Auntie and Uncle
have such a loving relationship.

16:04.040 --> 16:06.080
Congratulations, you noticed right away.

16:08.520 --> 16:09.760
Here, eat up.

16:10.240 --> 16:12.400
You should eat more and talk less.

16:13.840 --> 16:14.920
Eat...

16:15.200 --> 16:16.800
- Eat up.
- Hurry.

16:17.880 --> 16:18.840
Thanks.

16:24.320 --> 16:25.520
Xiao Nai!

16:26.880 --> 16:28.360
So sorry about that.

16:28.440 --> 16:29.920
Weiwei's Dad is acting weird.

16:30.000 --> 16:31.440
I don't know what's gotten into him.

16:31.520 --> 16:34.640
We were going to have you
room with him, but...

16:35.000 --> 16:36.600
It's okay. Thanks, Auntie.

16:37.280 --> 16:40.720
Well, get some rest soon.
Thanks for driving.

16:41.080 --> 16:43.400
Thanks for driving. Good night.

18:18.080 --> 18:20.240
DAILY LIVING

18:20.320 --> 18:24.280
DOES NOT SNORE

18:24.360 --> 18:27.840
NO STRANGE SMELL

18:38.480 --> 18:41.080
Young man, are you holding up?

18:41.600 --> 18:43.000
If so, then hurry!

18:47.200 --> 18:48.760
STAMINA: PASS

18:53.920 --> 18:56.160
Weiwei...

18:56.240 --> 18:57.320
Coming!

19:05.200 --> 19:06.160
What's going on?

19:07.680 --> 19:09.960
We ran into your aunt
giving us a sack of rice.

19:12.680 --> 19:15.000
And someone happens
to send a box of drinks?

19:16.920 --> 19:18.000
Correct!

19:19.320 --> 19:22.040
It's so hot. Honey?

19:28.720 --> 19:30.240
You put up with my dad?

19:32.720 --> 19:34.320
I think we should have a son.

19:38.120 --> 19:40.160
How did you jump to that conclusion?

19:40.240 --> 19:41.760
You haven't won my dad over.

19:44.040 --> 19:46.200
When Uncle made me run 5,000 meters,

19:46.400 --> 19:48.000
I was thinking,

19:48.640 --> 19:50.160
if we had a daughter,

19:50.520 --> 19:52.240
I would probably give

19:52.320 --> 19:55.240
our future son-in-law an even harder time.

19:57.680 --> 19:59.800
I've even come up with a plan.

20:00.040 --> 20:01.360
But if that happens,

20:01.640 --> 20:03.760
our daughter won't ever get married.

20:04.520 --> 20:06.040
So, it's better to have a son.

20:06.960 --> 20:09.440
I can show him how to net
someone else's daughter.

20:11.120 --> 20:13.280
I'm someone else's daughter, aren't I?

20:13.720 --> 20:17.120
Oh, no! I accidentally
let my missus find out.

20:19.200 --> 20:21.720
I'm not yours yet. I'll go talk to my dad.

20:37.000 --> 20:38.160
What's this?

20:42.720 --> 20:46.200
Comrade Old Bei,
are you sure this is a good idea?

20:47.080 --> 20:47.960
What?

20:49.960 --> 20:53.440
Sugar-coated bombs are useless.

20:57.480 --> 21:01.280
I'm telling you, you're letting
the romance get to your head.

21:01.600 --> 21:04.080
Your mom was sold,
as soon as she saw his pretty face.

21:05.240 --> 21:06.600
Right now,

21:06.960 --> 21:12.120
we need a clear-headed person
in the family, and that's me.

21:13.920 --> 21:15.000
Yes, Dad.

21:15.640 --> 21:19.600
I swear, he's not sugar-coated.
He's just a regular bomb.

21:20.720 --> 21:25.240
But Dad, don't you think
your requirement indicators

21:25.480 --> 21:28.160
- are a bit odd?
- Why are they odd?

21:30.880 --> 21:32.080
Schools want students who excel

21:32.160 --> 21:35.880
in moral, intellectual, physical,
art, and labor education, right?

21:37.760 --> 21:40.440
I'm looking for a son-in-law.

21:40.720 --> 21:42.480
Shouldn't my standards be even higher?

21:43.800 --> 21:45.200
But, Dad, just think,

21:45.400 --> 21:47.840
if Xiao Nai's parents
also assessed me the same way,

21:48.840 --> 21:51.840
- wouldn't you be upset?
- Of course! They can't do that.

21:55.120 --> 21:57.320
Kid, I'm being serious with you.

22:01.880 --> 22:05.840
Weiwei, I'm not trying to stop you,

22:06.720 --> 22:08.080
but marriage

22:08.160 --> 22:11.520
is a huge deal in a girl's life.

22:12.520 --> 22:15.640
I just want you
to give yourself more time.

22:15.720 --> 22:18.680
Seriously consider what you want
for your future self.

22:18.760 --> 22:21.360
Don't make a hasty decision.

22:24.120 --> 22:25.640
This guy, Xiao... Yes,

22:26.320 --> 22:28.320
he's good all-around
and he knows everything.

22:28.400 --> 22:33.000
You can say that he's even more perfect
than your dad, when I was young.

22:34.040 --> 22:39.000
But he's too perfect,
and that's worrisome.

22:40.560 --> 22:42.600
What kind of logic is that?

22:42.680 --> 22:45.160
Plus, he doesn't know everything.

22:45.240 --> 22:46.400
He can't cook, for one.

22:48.160 --> 22:49.400
He can't cook?

22:52.400 --> 22:55.400
All right, I'm telling you,
just this alone

22:55.480 --> 22:57.840
cancels out
all of his other finer qualities.

22:58.360 --> 22:59.280
No good.

23:00.440 --> 23:02.480
How can you do that, Dad?

23:02.560 --> 23:05.640
Once married, you'll do grocery shopping,
cooking, and waiting on him.

23:06.000 --> 23:06.840
No way.

23:07.480 --> 23:09.880
- Dad!
- I nearly forgot this point.

23:10.160 --> 23:12.520
It's a no-go, since he can't cook.

23:27.040 --> 23:30.240
I did more damage than good.
You're better off on your own.

23:31.600 --> 23:33.160
Let me go talk to Uncle.

23:43.080 --> 23:47.040
Mom, do you think Old Bei is giving
Xiao Nai a hard time?

23:48.800 --> 23:51.600
No, they've only been talking
for 10 minutes.

23:55.120 --> 23:56.760
Good. It's decided then.

23:57.560 --> 23:59.160
Weiwei, listen,

23:59.240 --> 24:02.080
if you want to get married, do it soon.

24:02.400 --> 24:03.760
As soon as you can.

24:07.280 --> 24:10.880
Wait, silly girl.
Why are you still sitting here?

24:11.160 --> 24:13.560
You two should go talk, go...

24:17.800 --> 24:20.480
- What's going on?
- Listen...

24:22.920 --> 24:24.720
What did you say to my dad?

24:24.800 --> 24:28.400
Why did he make an about-face
and now can't wait to marry me off?

24:29.320 --> 24:31.200
We talked about you as a kid.

24:32.080 --> 24:33.680
- That's it?
- Yes.

24:34.080 --> 24:36.040
Uncle seems to like kids a lot.

24:36.120 --> 24:38.200
I mentioned the relaxation
of the one-child policy,

24:38.280 --> 24:39.600
and that we can have two kids.

24:39.960 --> 24:43.760
If they all look like you,
they'll be adorable.

24:44.880 --> 24:47.840
What's that got to do with us
getting married now?

24:53.400 --> 24:54.880
Your Dad probably thinks

24:55.280 --> 24:57.680
it'd be nice to have two grandkids soon.

24:58.960 --> 25:00.520
Young people...

25:01.000 --> 25:04.240
Young people should get married soon.

25:05.560 --> 25:07.880
Get married soon, and have kids soon.

25:08.480 --> 25:11.280
She'll recover faster,
while she's young. No?

25:11.920 --> 25:12.760
You win.

25:13.000 --> 25:15.960
I'm about to be a grandfather!

25:16.440 --> 25:18.480
You mean, I'm about to be a grandmother?

25:18.560 --> 25:21.040
That's right!
Someone's about to be a grandmother!

25:21.960 --> 25:23.760
Come inside, Weiwei!

25:34.880 --> 25:38.920
Mom, it's a done deal.
You can come ask for her hand in marriage.

25:46.840 --> 25:49.960
- Your parents will be here tomorrow?
- Yes.

25:50.280 --> 25:51.760
So soon?

25:52.560 --> 25:55.600
Ms. Bei sounds reluctant.

25:56.560 --> 25:58.960
Ms. Bei thinks life is so unreal.

25:59.040 --> 26:00.760
I'm totally unprepared.

26:04.280 --> 26:08.280
My parents had wanted me
to go to Wuhan University.

26:08.640 --> 26:11.520
But I thought,
I'd never been to another city,

26:11.600 --> 26:13.160
so I applied for Qing University.

26:13.680 --> 26:16.040
If I'd gone to Wuhan University,

26:16.240 --> 26:18.360
I probably wouldn't have met you.

26:21.240 --> 26:24.280
- What are you thinking about?
- Parallel universe theory.

26:26.840 --> 26:29.040
Why are you thinking about that?

26:29.600 --> 26:33.360
I'm thinking,
if a parallel universe does exist,

26:34.640 --> 26:37.080
and that Bei Weiwei
went to Wuhan University,

26:37.760 --> 26:40.640
wouldn't that mean
that Xiao Nai would never get married?

26:46.320 --> 26:47.720
I'd pity him.

26:51.920 --> 26:54.880
Wouldn't he find someone else?

26:56.720 --> 26:58.160
He must be very picky.

27:01.680 --> 27:04.280
I think that Bei Weiwei
would be very picky, too.

27:07.240 --> 27:11.200
Anyway, life is long.
They'd eventually meet.

27:15.240 --> 27:18.160
Maybe in their sixties,

27:18.240 --> 27:20.120
when they're both old.

27:20.200 --> 27:22.480
One day, they'd meet
and spark a twilight romance.

27:24.160 --> 27:27.120
- Twilight romance?
- Yes.

27:27.400 --> 27:29.360
People in their 60s,

27:29.440 --> 27:33.000
both single, and they make do as a couple.

27:34.160 --> 27:35.000
Weiwei...

27:37.160 --> 27:38.800
Let's move up our wedding date.

27:40.640 --> 27:41.880
Why?

27:43.680 --> 27:46.120
Making up for the time lost
by the two sexagenarians.

27:51.480 --> 27:53.160
Making up for it in quality time.

28:18.480 --> 28:20.400
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

28:23.800 --> 28:24.800
Here... Eat up...

28:24.880 --> 28:26.600
- There's a lot of food.
- Help yourself.

28:26.680 --> 28:28.280
You're too kind.

28:28.360 --> 28:29.800
Eat up...

28:29.880 --> 28:32.120
- Here, have some.
- Right...

28:36.520 --> 28:39.440
- Eat up! It's good stuff.
- Eat up, Xiao Nai.

28:44.960 --> 28:46.880
It's so lovely!

28:50.320 --> 28:53.440
Weiwei, I love this style.

28:53.520 --> 28:55.080
Simple and classy.

28:55.760 --> 28:57.120
When I get married,

28:57.200 --> 28:59.080
will Lord design my home?

28:59.160 --> 29:02.360
Me, too! I love your interior design.

29:02.920 --> 29:05.440
I helped, too. I can design your place.

29:05.920 --> 29:07.960
Your designs are old-fashioned.

29:10.040 --> 29:11.320
You're shallow!

29:11.400 --> 29:13.480
I did the interior design with Lord.

29:13.560 --> 29:15.560
You had to give him all the credit.

29:16.280 --> 29:18.520
Weiwei, bring out your wedding gown!

29:18.600 --> 29:21.600
- We came to see the wedding gown.
- Exactly!

29:24.520 --> 29:27.000
You can go see it in the bedroom.
I can't carry it.

29:27.080 --> 29:28.960
- You can't carry it?
- What?

29:29.440 --> 29:30.680
Where's the bedroom?

29:50.000 --> 29:51.440
The phoenix coronet?

29:52.120 --> 29:54.000
This bridal headdress is gorgeous!

29:54.080 --> 29:55.600
I thought it'd be like a cap.

29:55.680 --> 29:57.000
I don't like those.

29:57.280 --> 29:59.400
Those are good, too, just too heavy.

29:59.480 --> 30:01.520
How much did this cost?

30:01.600 --> 30:04.560
I don't know. You'd have to ask him.
More than 100,000?

30:05.480 --> 30:08.680
My goodness! You'll be wearing
a bathroom on your head!

30:09.920 --> 30:11.720
Can't you say something nice?

30:11.800 --> 30:13.920
He said this won't depreciate in value.

30:14.000 --> 30:15.280
So it's not a waste of money.

30:15.360 --> 30:18.240
Right? Lord's wedding
can't be haphazard, can it?

30:18.600 --> 30:21.200
Even if Weiwei does wear
a bathroom on her head,

30:21.280 --> 30:22.720
it'd be okay.

30:23.160 --> 30:24.600
So, it doesn't depreciate in value,

30:24.680 --> 30:26.760
but it won't lay eggs. Is it worth it?

30:26.840 --> 30:29.520
Weiwei will lay eggs.

30:30.960 --> 30:32.800
I have offspring, not eggs. Okay?

30:33.800 --> 30:37.600
I love this. It's so pretty.

30:38.240 --> 30:39.400
I don't get it.

30:39.480 --> 30:42.440
Why do we wear white wedding gowns
like Westerners?

30:42.520 --> 30:45.680
Our traditional phoenix coronet
and robe of rank are prettier.

30:45.760 --> 30:48.800
That's right. I used to love
the outfits in martial arts films.

30:49.080 --> 30:52.320
I'd wrap myself in a blanket
and pretend I'm wearing period costume.

30:53.360 --> 30:55.320
Put it on and let us see!

30:56.160 --> 30:57.400
I don't know how to wear this.

30:57.480 --> 30:58.880
- What?
- What?

30:59.360 --> 31:01.600
- Do you know how? Huh?
- No, not me.

31:04.240 --> 31:06.640
Weiwei is getting married so soon!

31:07.120 --> 31:10.880
Not soon, I'm registered already.

31:21.120 --> 31:22.360
Let's see! Hurry!

31:23.760 --> 31:26.400
This has got to be the prettiest
marriage registration photo.

31:26.680 --> 31:29.720
Girl, what's the hurry?

31:29.800 --> 31:31.200
Are you pregnant?

31:31.720 --> 31:32.840
- Let me see!
- If I don't hurry,

31:32.920 --> 31:34.760
you might run off with a certain diplomat.

31:34.840 --> 31:37.120
Then I might not get
a red envelop from you!

31:37.200 --> 31:40.080
Don't mention that rascal Cao Guang!

31:40.200 --> 31:43.400
I must have lost my mind, to apply for
the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.

31:43.880 --> 31:47.080
I didn't mention Cao Guang.
I only said a certain diplomat.

31:49.800 --> 31:52.240
I'll bite you!

31:52.920 --> 31:56.000
Okay... Enough, it's just Cao Guang.

31:56.320 --> 31:57.600
And you!

32:05.080 --> 32:08.080
Don't walk us out.
We'll get a cab downstairs.

32:08.440 --> 32:09.600
I wasn't going to.

32:09.680 --> 32:11.680
- You're awful!
- You're visiting?

32:20.920 --> 32:22.800
Mr. Xiao...

32:23.360 --> 32:25.160
We're leaving now. We won't disturb you.

32:27.320 --> 32:30.360
You're going to have a wedding soon.

32:30.440 --> 32:32.560
Should you be living together?

32:34.120 --> 32:37.240
Why don't you permit Weiwei
to stay with us at Xiaoling's tonight?

32:38.600 --> 32:40.560
I need permission to stay out overnight?

32:40.880 --> 32:42.040
Maybe not tonight.

32:44.120 --> 32:45.920
I thought you didn't need permission?

32:47.720 --> 32:49.520
It's getting late. I'll drive you home.

32:51.120 --> 32:52.640
Okay, don't play shy.

32:52.720 --> 32:54.800
I'll let you look at him
a little longer today.

32:55.960 --> 32:58.080
Don't be silly. We're not shy about that.

32:58.160 --> 32:59.680
- Right?
- Bye-bye...

32:59.760 --> 33:01.960
- Bye-bye!
- Bye-bye! See you.

34:51.000 --> 34:53.040
You're back already?

34:53.120 --> 34:55.520
- Their place...
- The wedding gown's here?

34:57.760 --> 34:59.320
It arrived this afternoon.

35:04.600 --> 35:09.120
I went to take a shower,
and I thought the dress was a bit dirty.

35:09.200 --> 35:11.160
So I wanted to wash it,

35:12.280 --> 35:14.280
but I don't know how to wear it.

35:15.520 --> 35:17.560
I do. I'll put it on you.

35:27.920 --> 35:29.160
This is the first piece.

38:33.520 --> 38:35.960
Weiwei, I can't wait any longer.

38:50.040 --> 38:53.160
Weiwei, let me show you a place.

39:27.040 --> 39:29.000
Tomorrow, all these computers
will be cleared out.

39:31.000 --> 39:32.480
The place is shutting down?

39:33.840 --> 39:35.400
I'll move Zhiyi's office here.

39:35.960 --> 39:37.600
I already bought the place.

39:44.080 --> 39:47.880
Fantastic!
It's best to have your own place.

39:50.560 --> 39:53.840
That will be the conference room.
This is the office area.

39:53.920 --> 39:55.840
There will be a small kitchen.

39:56.520 --> 40:00.920
The space in the back will be
an open entertainment area.

40:04.600 --> 40:07.320
When I first saw you,
you were sitting right there.

40:20.040 --> 40:23.000
It was love at first sight for you,
wasn't it?

40:28.240 --> 40:32.880
I just now realized, you're a total lech.

40:38.600 --> 40:39.440
Do you disagree?

40:41.720 --> 40:45.320
No, but it doesn't quite do me justice.

40:48.960 --> 40:53.040
I'm at least a voracious lech.

40:53.840 --> 40:56.400
You're not ashamed? You're proud of it?

40:57.840 --> 41:00.560
As a picky, non-omnivorous lech,

41:01.520 --> 41:04.800
it's more shameful to not be voracious.

41:07.760 --> 41:09.320
Let me check out the back.

41:55.640 --> 41:58.720
This can be Lord's office.

41:59.400 --> 42:00.720
Right, Lord?

42:14.880 --> 42:17.480
Hey! What are you doing?

42:17.960 --> 42:19.720
Thinking about your earlier question.

42:20.480 --> 42:23.200
Did I ask you a question?

42:28.640 --> 42:33.920
I'm thinking,
if I'd known what I know now,

42:36.320 --> 42:38.400
I'd definitely be in love,
at the first sight of you.

45:30.400 --> 45:32.840
Subtitle translation by Lu Yuhan
